!Sample_title = CITE-seq ADT  library from mobilized peripheral CD34+ HSPC donor 31800 at Day 3
!Sample_geo_accession = GSM9170330
!Sample_status = Public on Oct 23 2025
!Sample_submission_date = Aug 13 2025
!Sample_last_update_date = Oct 23 2025
!Sample_type = SRA
!Sample_channel_count = 1
!Sample_source_name_ch1 = peripheral blood
!Sample_organism_ch1 = Homo sapiens
!Sample_taxid_ch1 = 9606
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = tissue: peripheral blood
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = cell type: CD34-positive hematopoietic stem and progenitor cell
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = treatment: StemSpan SFEM media supplemented with CC100 and thrombopoietin (TPO), cultured for 10 days with media changes every 2-3 days
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = batch: donor 31800
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = time point: Day 3
!Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1 = Cells were maintained in standard culture conditions with StemSpan SFEM media supplemented with CC100 and thrombopoietin (TPO). No additional treatments or stimulations were applied. Cells were sampled at five time points: day 2 day 3 day 4 day 7 and day 10 of culture.
!Sample_growth_protocol_ch1 = Mobilized peripheral CD34+ hematopoietic stem and progenitor cells (HSPCs) were obtained from four healthy human donors. Cells were cultured in StemSpan SFEM media supplemented with CC100 cytokine cocktail and thrombopoietin (TPO) at 37Â¬âC with 5% CO2. Media was changed every 2-3 days during the 10-day culture period. No additional media supplements were added to the cell culture conditions.
!Sample_molecule_ch1 = protein
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = Total RNA was extracted from single cells using the 10x Genomics protocol. For CITE-seq samples cell surface proteins were captured using TotalSeq-B Human Universal Cocktail V1.0 antibodies before cell lysis. For Multiome samples nuclei were isolated for ATAC-seq library preparation following the 10x Genomics protocol.
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = CITE-seq libraries were prepared using 10x Genomics Single Cell Gene Expression with Feature Barcoding technology version 3.1. Two libraries were generated per sample: gene expression (GEX) using standard 3' single cell RNA-seq and surface protein detection using antibody-derived tags (ADT) with TotalSeq-B antibodies. Multiome libraries were prepared using 10x Genomics Chromium Single Cell Multiome ATAC + Gene Expression technology generating paired GEX and ATAC libraries from the same cells.
!Sample_description = Library name: SRAB0001971
!Sample_description = CITE-seq ADT  library from mobilized peripheral CD34+ HSPC donor 31800 at Day 3
!Sample_description = 10x Genomics Single Cell Gene Expression with Feature Barcoding technology (CITE-seq) using TotalSeq-B Human Universal Cocktail V1.0. Time course analysis of mobilized peripheral CD34+ hematopoietic stem and progenitor cells cultured in StemSpan SFEM media with CC100 and TPO. Cells collected at day 2 of 10-day culture period. Cell types include HSC, MasP, MkP, NeuP, MoP, EryP, and BP based on preliminary annotation.
!Sample_description = CITE_donor_31800_day_3.h5mu
!Sample_description = citeseq_protein_counts.h5ad
!Sample_description = citeseq_alldonors_alldays.h5ad
!Sample_data_processing = Raw sequencing reads were processed using Cell Ranger for CITE-seq samples and Cell Ranger ARC  for Multiome samples to generate count matrices.
!Sample_data_processing = Quality control filtering was applied to remove low-quality cells and genes. Cells with high mitochondrial gene expression or low total gene counts were excluded.
!Sample_data_processing = Count matrices were normalized and log-transformed. For CITE-seq protein data CLR (centered log-ratio) normalization was applied.
!Sample_data_processing = Cell type annotation was performed using gene expression signatures based on reference: https://www.nature.com/articles/ncb3493. Cell types identified include: HSC (Hematopoietic Stem Cell) MasP (Mast Cell Progenitor) MkP (Megakaryocyte Progenitor) NeuP (Neutrophil Progenitor) MoP (Monocyte Progenitor) EryP (Erythrocyte Progenitor) and BP (B-Cell Progenitor).
